df['Team'] = df['Team'].replace({'-': 'NO'})
df['Base'] = df['Base'].replace({'-': 0})
df['Sold'] = df['Sold'].replace({'TBA': 0, 'Unsold': 0})
df['Base'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Base'], errors='coerce')
df['Sold'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Sold'], errors='coerce')
df.info()

# Statistical measures for 'Sold' column
mean_Sold = df["Sold"].mean()
median_Sold = df["Sold"].median()
mode_Sold = df["Sold"].mode()[0]  # Mode can have multiple values; picking the first one
variance_Sold = df["Sold"].var()
std_Sold = df["Sold"].std()
range_Sold = df["Sold"].max() - df["Sold"].min()

# Print the results
print(f"Mean: {mean_Sold}")
print(f"Median: {median_Sold}")
print(f"Mode: {mode_Sold}")
print(f"Variance: {variance_Sold}")
print(f"Standard Deviation: {std_Sold}")
print(f"Range: {range_Sold}")

In [23]:
# Avoid division by zero
df['multiplier'] = df['Sold'] / df['Base'].replace(0, pd.NA)

# Drop NaN multipliers (players not sold or base = 0)
df1 = df.dropna(subset=['multiplier'])

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
sns.histplot(df1['multiplier'], bins=30, kde=True, color='darkorange')
plt.title('Distribution of Sold/Base Price Multipliers')
plt.xlabel('Multiplier (Sold  Base)')
plt.ylabel('Number of Players')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Aggregate team spend by player type
team_type_spend = df.pivot_table(index='Team', columns='Type', values='Sold', aggfunc='sum', fill_value=0)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.heatmap(team_type_spend, annot=True, fmt=".1f", cmap='YlGnBu')
plt.title('Team-wise Spending by Player Type ( Cr)')
plt.xlabel('Player Type')
plt.ylabel('Team')
plt.show()

# Top 10 most expensive players
top_costliest = df.sort_values(by='Sold', ascending=False).head(10)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(data=top_costliest, y='Players', x='Sold', palette='rocket')
plt.title('Top 10 Costliest Players (Sold Price)')
plt.xlabel('Sold Price ( Cr)')
plt.ylabel('Player Name')
plt.show()

# Top 10 highest multipliers
top_multipliers = df.sort_values(by='multiplier', ascending=False).head(10)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(data=top_multipliers, y='Players', x='multiplier', palette='coolwarm')
plt.title('Top 10 Highest Multipliers (Sold  Base)')
